grabs a security news story and description from TechCrunch.

Usage: %s [OPTIONS]\n\n" $self
Fetches security news stories from TechCrunch
Options:
-n, --num NUMBER     Number of stories to fetch (1-50, default: 1)
-s, --sort TYPE      Sort order: 'recent' or 'older' (default: recent)
-f, --format TYPE    Output format: 'brief' or 'detailed' (default: brief)
-h, --help           Show this help message
Example: -n 10 -s recent -f detailed